name: Gnarly Mountain Cookies - Colorado Sweet Corn
description:
The only way to perfect the corn muffin was to make it into a cookie with a little extra honey. Just the right amount of sweetness for a morning snack. Just the right amount of sweetness for a holiday dessert. Featuring Bow & Arrow Brand Whole Grain Cornmeal.


Ingredients: Butter, All-Purpose Flour, Brown Sugar, Pasteurized Egg, Granulated Sugar, Iodized Salt, Baking Soda, Bow & Arrow Brand Whole Grain Cornmeal, Honey, Freeze Dried Corn, Vanilla Extract


Allergens: Egg, Gluten

name: Gnarly Mountain Cookies - Horchata
description:
The wonderful horchata flavor was made for cookies. This cookie was designed for a morning treat, but it can be enjoyed all hours of the day. Cinnamon ALL DAY Cookie monsters!


Ingredients: Butter, All-Purpose Flour, Brown Sugar, Pasteurized Egg, Granulated Sugar, Iodized Salt, Baking Soda, Horchata Powder (Dextrose, Sugar, Titanium Dioxide, Maltodextrin, Partially Hydrogenated Vegetable Oil (May Contain Soybean and/or Canola and/or Palm Oil), Skimmed Milk Powder, Artificial Flavor, Guar Gum, Silicon Dioxide, Aspartame, Powdered Cinnamon, Rice Flour, Acesulfame, Potassium, Ascorbic Acid (Vitamin C) and Caramel), White Chips, Butter Scotch Chips, Rum Extract, Cinnamon, Vanilla Extract

description:
Our very own lemon cookie with a smooth vanilla and citrus glaze topped with candied lemon zest. Your taste buds will thank you again and again.

description:
We just couldn't resist using sweet cherries, smooth vanilla, and Rocky Mountain Soda Company's Root Beer for our Root Beer Float Cookie. After one bite, you'll go back in time and remember one of the best parts of your childhood. No straw necessary!!

name: Dis Burrito Breakfast Burrito - Bacon
description:
While the bacon burrito follows the traditional recipe for a bacon breakfast burrito, there is nothing traditional about this delicious staple. Our Premium Bacon is cooked to perfection and never fried. Carefully layered across the tortilla with roasted potatoes, real cheese blend, 100% real egg and house made veggie green chili, to make sure you taste every ingredient with every bite. Just a bacon burrito? I think not....just might be your favorite of all time.


Burritos must be heated to an internal Temperature of 165 degrees.


For heating:

Oven: 325 degrees for 20-25 minutes

Microwave to press: microwave 60 seconds, then place in panini press at 450 degrees / 90 seconds. 

Press: 4-5 minutes until internal temp is 165 degrees. 

Microwave: cook 90 seconds, flip and cook for 30 more seconds.


Case of 12 Burritos


Click here for Dis Burrito Tres Verde Sauce!

name: Dis Burrito Breakfast Burrito - Chicken Chorizo
description:
Not all meat eaters eat pork. And why are most breakfast meats pork anyway. Maybe because the other options never seem to be executed correctly. Dis Burrito has designed a chicken chorizo breakfast burrito with your belly and taste buds in mind. Start with All Natural Red Bird ground chicken and slow cook it with a secret blend of herbs and spices. Then you pair it with the traditional burrito fixin’s of; fresh roasted potatoes, real egg(not egg product), 100% cheese blend and house made veggie green chili, and you get... fresh, flavorful and foxy burritos in your belly.


Burritos must be heated to an internal Temperature of 165 degrees.


For heating:

Oven: 325 degrees for 20-25 minutes

Microwave to press: microwave 60 seconds, then place in panini press at 450 degrees / 90 seconds. 

Press: 4-5 minutes until internal temp is 165 degrees. 

Microwave: cook 90 seconds, flip and cook for 30 more seconds.

name: Dis Burrito Breakfast Burrito - Pork Breakfast Sausage
description:
Polidari Denver provides us with such a fantastic flavor of their pork breakfast sausage that it’s pure bliss. When you add the traditional ingredients (roasted potatoes, housemade green chili, 100% egg (no egg product) and a real cheese blend), specially curated for your taste buds you get pure heaven.

name: Dis Burrito Breakfast Burrito - Veggie (Black Bean)
description:
Many places claim to have a veggie burrito, but consequently they put pork green chili or chicken stock in their sauces. Not at Dis Burrito. We make sure our veggie burrito only Contains Lacto/Ovo-vegetarian ingredients. For those wondering, Lacto = dairy and Ovo = Eggs. This means our Veggie burrito does contain cheese and egg, however the rest of the ingredients, roasted potatoes, black beans, and veggie green chili, will meet all the needs of the Lacto/Ovo vegetarian.

name: Dis Burrito Breakfast Burrito - Plant-Based Chorizo (Vegan)
description:
At Dis Burrito we feel that all eaters deserve to have the best of the best, and our plant based is no different. Instead of omitting ingredients, we partner with the highest quality replacements, so you feel like you are eating the best burrito you have ever had. We use Violife for the cheese, Ju|st for the Egg, and RollinGreens for the pea protein. We apply our proprietary blend of chorizo spices and you have the best plant based burrito you can find. Add the roasted potatoes on our veggie Hatch green chili, on boom!!!! The best part is it hits 3 markets: Vegan’s, folks allergic to eggs, and those who are lactose intolerant.


Burritos must be heated to an internal Temperature of 165 degrees.

name: Dis Burrito Breakfast Burrito - Gluten-Free Veggie (Black Bean)
description:
If you are going to make a gluten free burrito, you might as well do it right. We partnered with the best GF tortilla manufacturer we could find. The Siete Foods cassava flour tortilla sets the mark when it comes to GF tortillas. Our veggie burrito does contain cheese and egg, however the rest of the ingredients, roasted potatoes, black beans, and veggie green chili, will meet all the needs of the Gluten Free Vegetarian. Or its great for just regular ole’ eatin’ cuz most folks can't even tell.
